  "prompt": "Who are the best 5 left handed fast bowlers in Indian domestic cricket after Zaheer Khan's retirement?",
  "response": "Identifying the definitive \"best\" is always subjective and based on different criteria. However, considering factors like performance in Ranji Trophy, Vijay Hazare Trophy, Deodhar Trophy, IPL, consistency, and potential, here are 5 left-arm fast bowlers who have made a mark in Indian domestic cricket since Zaheer Khan's retirement:\n\n1.  **Jaydev Unadkat:** Arguably the most successful left-arm pacer in Indian domestic cricket post-Zaheer. He has been a consistent performer for Saurashtra for years. He holds the record for most wickets in a single Ranji Trophy season (67). Unadkat has also led Saurashtra to Ranji Trophy titles. He has the experience of playing for India across formats. His experience, leadership, and ability to swing the ball make him a standout.\n\n2.  **Barinder Sran:** Sran had a brief stint with the Indian national team but has been a consistent performer in domestic cricket. He plays for Punjab and is known for his pace and ability to generate bounce. His IPL stints have also been quite successful. He is known for his ability to bowl at high pace and can trouble batsmen with his awkward angle.\n\n3.  **Aniket Choudhary:** Choudhary has been a mainstay in the Rajasthan bowling attack.  He has the ability to move the ball both ways. He was also a net bowler for the Indian team and has been recognized for his potential. He consistently takes wickets in Ranji Trophy and has been a key member of his state team.\n\n4. **T Natarajan:** While predominantly known for his T20 exploits, Natarajan came through the Tamil Nadu ranks in domestic cricket. He is known for his yorker skills and has had considerable success in the IPL. While he might not have a long first-class record, his impact and skill set make him a worthy mention, especially considering the growing importance of white-ball cricket.\n\n5.  **Lukman Meriwala:** Lukman Meriwala from Baroda is another promising left-arm pacer who has shown good potential.  He is known for his variations and has been able to make an impact in limited-overs cricket in the domestic circuit. He has also played a few IPL games\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Subjectivity:** This list is based on performance, potential, and impact. Other bowlers might have arguments for inclusion.\n*   **Focus on Impact:** These bowlers have consistently performed at the domestic level and some have had success in IPL.\n*   **Evolving Landscape:** Indian domestic cricket is constantly evolving, so new talent is always emerging.\n\nThis list represents a good starting point for identifying impactful left-arm fast bowlers in Indian domestic cricket after Zaheer Khan. You can further refine it based on your own criteria and preferences.\n",
